1
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:36,320
Look.

2
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:40,840
How could there be such a good thing?

3
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:43,000
It says clearly in the newspaper.

4
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:45,080
Let me see.

5
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:48,080
The guide agency has already arranged work for me.

6
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:50,160
I'm going to see a client at Xinya Hotel tomorrow.

7
00:01:50,160 --> 00:01:51,800
I also bought a map of the concession.

8
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:53,280
I have to study it carefully when I get back

9
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,200
to learn Shanghai's geography

10
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,640
and where the nice views are.

11
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:56,720
Why are you reading a book?

12
00:01:56,720 --> 00:01:58,200
You can just ask me.

13
00:01:58,320 --> 00:01:58,880
Ask you?

14
00:01:59,080 --> 00:02:00,280
You are not an old Shanghai hand.

15
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:02,010
I can also speak Shanghainese.

16
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:03,880
What kind of accent is that?

17
00:02:03,880 --> 00:02:05,280
Doesn't it sound like it?

18
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:08,979
I have something good for you.

19
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:23,000
This milk powder is very expensive.

20
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:23,860
Did you forget?

21
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:25,600
I have a slush fund.

22
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:28,520
But I haven't even paid you back for the last time.

23
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:29,600
So what?

24
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:32,079
You have a job now anyway.

25
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:34,850
We can't let our little Yueming go hungry.

26
00:02:37,079 --> 00:02:38,410
We are making money now.

27
00:02:38,920 --> 00:02:40,440
Things will get better soon.

28
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:41,079
Right.

29
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:43,120
Then keep a clear record of every sum.

30
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:44,280
I will pay you back all at once later.

31
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,120
I am keeping track.

32
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:46,000
I have everything recorded.

33
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:48,040
Okay, I'll go back now.

34
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:49,570
I still have homework to do.

35
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:50,600
Goodbye.

36
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:52,360
See you.

37
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:53,560
Thank you.

38
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:55,000
See you.

39
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:25,480
What?

40
00:04:58,080 --> 00:05:00,760
Expel the Japanese invaders.

41
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:32,860
We'll start from scratch,

42
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:35,120
reclaim our old land,

43
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:38,000
and report to the Emperor.

44
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:12,720
This doesn't look like Hetian jade.

45
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:16,960
It's just a rock from the roadside.

46
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:18,520
There are plenty of them by the Huangpu River.

47
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:19,120
If you like it,

48
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:20,380
I can send you a basket.

49
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:26,920
It smells a bit fishy.

50
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:28,180
After all that,

51
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:28,840
why is there

52
00:06:28,840 --> 00:06:30,800
only this torn book?

53
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:34,159
Torn book?

54
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,600
'Records of Mount Lu'.

55
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:42,880
You have to trust Uncle's taste.

56
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:45,450
The rare books Uncle collected

57
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:46,680
are good stuff.

58
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,970
We have to get our hands on them.

59
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,520
That's what I said.

60
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:53,920
Your uncle has been in the concession

61
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:55,240
for over a month.

62
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:58,040
How could he return in one piece?

63
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:00,440
Now I see it clearly.

64
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,570
The biggest scoundrel here

65
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,920
is that punk named Meng.

66
00:07:05,840 --> 00:07:07,880
He teamed up with Uncle and Sister-in-law

67
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:09,320
to play tricks

68
00:07:09,880 --> 00:07:11,340
and deceive us for so long.

69
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:13,760
We were too honest,

70
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:15,480
so we were fooled.

71
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:19,760
Honest people have their blessings.

72
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:22,760
Losing the title deed

73
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:25,200
might not be a bad thing.

74
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:26,400
What do you mean?

75
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:27,730
Without the title deed,

76
00:07:27,960 --> 00:07:29,600
how can they still dare to act

77
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:30,800
so arrogant in front of us?

78
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:31,920
Just tear up.

79
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:32,600
Kick them out.

80
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,440
No.

81
00:07:33,880 --> 00:07:34,880
He's my uncle.

82
00:07:34,920 --> 00:07:36,280
He watched me grow up.

83
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:37,240
Tear up? Kick them out?

84
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:38,100
I can't do that.

85
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:39,080
We can't do such a thing

86
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:40,400
that destroys morality.

87
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:41,840
What morality?

88
00:07:42,159 --> 00:07:43,200
They were unkind first,

89
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:44,360
so we are unjust later.

90
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:45,890
It's perfectly justified.

91
00:07:46,159 --> 00:07:48,159
Their family is completely ruined.

92
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:49,480
I don't think

93
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:50,960
they can make a comeback.

94
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:51,720
What?

95
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:54,040
Are you going to enshrine them

96
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:55,200
like Bodhisattvas

97
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,560
and burn incense for them every day?

98
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:57,480
Yeah.

99
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:01,040
Although they were unkind first,

100
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:03,800
we can't be unjust later.

101
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:05,880
No.

102
00:08:06,440 --> 00:08:08,000
We can't be unjust.

103
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:10,530
We have to find a way to make others unjust.

104
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:11,680
You confused me.

105
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:13,610
What exactly are you trying to say?

106
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:21,440
We can make the Japanese unjust.

107
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:25,680
You have such great ability?

108
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,480
Make Fujita unjust.

109
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:31,680
The first bowl:

110
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:36,880
Braised Pork with White Croaker.

111
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:38,559
The second bowl:

112
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:41,039
Pan-fried Fish.

113
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:46,080
Shuyuan, Yunqi,

114
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:46,560
Sister-in-law.

115
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:47,400
are you in the room?

116
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:47,880
Quick.

117
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:50,800
Yes, sister-in-law.

118
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:52,080
Wait,

119
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:52,880
wait a minute.

120
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:54,570
Sister-in-law,

121
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:55,640
you're here.

122
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:02,770
You're all here.

123
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,130
Sister-in-law,

124
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:05,160
what's wrong?

125
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:07,400
I... I'm fine.

126
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:09,800
Did you eat something toxic?

127
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:11,400
Your...

128
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:12,640
Mouth...

129
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:19,240
I...

130
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:21,080
I bought you gifts.

131
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:22,280
I was afraid it wouldn't taste good,

132
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:23,760
so I tried a little.

133
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:25,700
You scared me to death.

134
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:28,160
Why are you giving gifts when it's not a holiday?

135
00:09:28,160 --> 00:09:29,290
Come in and sit down.

136
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:32,120
Do you want to wash up?

137
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:34,320
It's fine.

138
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:41,840
I went to

139
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:44,360
Hujiang Guide Agency for an interview today.

140
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:44,960
They said

141
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:46,740
I can start working tomorrow.

142
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:49,000
Then...

143
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:50,760
Congratulations, sister-in-law.

144
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:51,880
Thanks to Yunqi.

145
00:09:52,560 --> 00:09:53,240
He told me

146
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:54,840
to buy reference books.

147
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:57,320
I did my homework when I came back at night.

148
00:09:57,320 --> 00:09:58,680
Then when I went there today,

149
00:09:58,680 --> 00:09:59,960
the people from the guide agency

150
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,090
were very satisfied

151
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:02,040
and very happy.

152
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:03,040
And

153
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:05,200
they even gave me an A.

154
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:06,680
I peeked.

155
00:10:08,680 --> 00:10:09,480
So,

156
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:10,840
I got the job.

157
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:11,960
I thought I must

158
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:13,960
buy a gift to thank you.

159
00:10:14,160 --> 00:10:16,680
But I didn't have much money,

160
00:10:16,840 --> 00:10:17,400
so

161
00:10:17,760 --> 00:10:18,690
I prepared this.

162
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,600
Although it's not expensive,

163
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:22,200
I hope you don't mind.

164
00:10:22,520 --> 00:10:24,450
Sister-in-law, how could we mind?

165
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:26,320
Since I was little,

166
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:27,560
I heard the elders say

167
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:29,160
that black food is nourishing.

168
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:30,960
They say red enters the heart,

169
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,040
green enters the liver,

170
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:33,040
yellow enters the spleen,

171
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:33,800
white enters the lungs,

172
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:34,760
and black enters the kidneys.

173
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:36,000
I... I...

174
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,040
Black enters me,

175
00:10:37,040 --> 00:10:38,000
I enter black.

176
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:39,880
This is also good for hair.

177
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:40,880
So I bought

178
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:43,280
black rice, black sesame, black beans, and the like,

179
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:45,400
asked them to cook it,

180
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:47,240
and then found a traditional Chinese medicine shop

181
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:48,570
to grind it into powder.

182
00:10:48,920 --> 00:10:51,280
But the assistant at the shop

183
00:10:51,280 --> 00:10:52,840
didn't know how to mix it.

184
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:55,000
We had to try it over and over again.

185
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:56,640
I tasted it after every mix.

186
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:58,170
I tasted it after every mix.

187
00:10:58,240 --> 00:10:59,480
But the taste was always wrong.

188
00:10:59,480 --> 00:11:01,340
But when I mixed it the sixth time,

189
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:03,560
It's the taste of my childhood.

190
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:05,600
The elderly in my hometown

191
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:07,480
all eat this to nourish their bodies.

192
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:09,280
Moreover, the 'Yellow Emperor's Inner Classic'

193
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:10,200
also says so.

194
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:11,880
So it must be effective.

195
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:12,980
Then I thought,

196
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:13,920
Yunqi,

197
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:15,620
you work in a foreign firm.

198
00:11:15,880 --> 00:11:18,640
Sometimes you must be busy with work

199
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:20,640
and don't have time to eat, right?

200
00:11:20,640 --> 00:11:22,280
Eating irregularly

201
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:23,540
is bad for your health.

202
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:26,960
So if you ever feel hungry

203
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:28,800
but don't have time,

204
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:30,920
just take a spoonful.

205
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:33,960
Eat it dry?

206
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:36,200
You can eat it dry. I've tried it.

207
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:38,520
It tastes fine.

208
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:41,520
And I added a little sugar.

209
00:11:41,640 --> 00:11:43,300
You can also add boiling water

210
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:44,650
and stir it into a paste.

211
00:11:44,880 --> 00:11:46,480
It tastes great that way too.

212
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:48,160
Shuyuan, you should eat it too.

213
00:11:48,160 --> 00:11:49,620
It's good for your health.

214
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:50,840
Okay.

215
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:52,400
Thank you, Sister-in-law.

216
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:53,840
Don't say thank you.

217
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:56,480
I should be the one thanking you.

218
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:01,080
I'll be leaving now.

219
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:03,560
I ran into A'yuan downstairs just now.

220
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:04,320
He said Nanny Jing

221
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:06,000
took Yueming out for some sun.

222
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:07,000
I'll go pick up Yueming.

223
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:08,120
I won't disturb you two any longer.

224
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:08,680
Alright.

225
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:10,160
Thank you.

226
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,160
Shuyuan.

227
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:21,360
Us becoming a family

228
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:23,440
is also destiny, right?

229
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:26,120
But look at how

230
00:12:26,560 --> 00:12:28,280
I treated you before.

231
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:34,080
Anyway,

232
00:12:36,160 --> 00:12:37,200
thank you.

233
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:44,360
I'm leaving now.

234
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:46,880
Goodbye, Yunqi.

235
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:13,840
This is delicious.

236
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:18,240
Look at how insanely dirty your face is.

237
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:20,600
Smells so good.

238
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:23,760
Shuyuan,

239
00:13:24,280 --> 00:13:25,920
Sister-in-law treats us so well,

240
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:27,380
but we treat her like this.

241
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:29,500
Aren't we being too inhumane?

242
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:31,360
When she held my hand just now,

243
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:32,620
for that brief moment,

244
00:13:33,160 --> 00:13:34,620
I felt a tingle in my heart,

245
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:36,660
which was really uncomfortable.

246
00:13:36,880 --> 00:13:37,560
I'd rather she just

247
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:39,290
push the door open and scold me.

248
00:13:39,440 --> 00:13:41,440
Then I could keep fighting with her.

249
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:44,260
This passive-aggressiveness is too annoying.

250
00:13:46,440 --> 00:13:47,040
Come.

251
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:48,960
Have a taste.

252
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:57,560
Is it sweet?

253
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:00,480
Or else,

254
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:01,800
let's just drop it

255
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:03,130
and not drive them away.

256
00:14:03,320 --> 00:14:05,040
Bullshit. Why should we?

257
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:08,800
Every man for himself.

258
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:12,320
Let me tell you,

259
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:14,330
if you don't secure this house,

260
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:15,720
you still want a son?

261
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:17,320
In your dreams!

262
00:14:20,440 --> 00:14:22,600
If we really feel guilty in our hearts,

263
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:24,480
we can be more diligent later

264
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:26,600
and visit Uncle and Sister-in-law more often.

265
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:27,640
Then I can also

266
00:14:27,640 --> 00:14:29,360
buy her supplements to nourish her body.

267
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:31,280
Deer horn, lingzhi, American ginseng,

268
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:32,800
cordyceps, and donkey-hide gelatin.

269
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:33,480
If all else fails,

270
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:35,480
I'll buy Sister-in-law a mink coat.

271
00:14:35,840 --> 00:14:37,440
I'll return all these favors to her.

272
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:38,500
Isn't that enough?

273
00:14:38,760 --> 00:14:39,960
You said it yourself.

274
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:40,920
Hurry up.

275
00:14:40,920 --> 00:14:42,000
While Uncle is still asleep,

276
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,240
return this box.

277
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:44,480
Otherwise, we'll be exposed.

278
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:45,480
Let's go together.

279
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:46,280
Who is 'we'?

280
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:47,200
I'm not going, you go.

281
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:48,160
Then I won't go.

282
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:49,560
I'll count to three.

283
00:14:49,560 --> 00:14:50,320
Three.

284
00:14:53,920 --> 00:14:55,160
Clean your face.

285
00:14:56,760 --> 00:14:58,400
I'm already this insanely dirty,

286
00:14:58,400 --> 00:14:59,730
who cares about my face?

287
00:16:06,080 --> 00:16:07,680
Silun,

288
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:20,480
writing quietly in the pavilion.

289
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:33,360
The water clock drips long in the bell and drum tower.

290
00:16:43,160 --> 00:16:45,240
The eaves bells ring,

