00:28:06,360 --> 00:28:07,090
some people.

589
00:28:07,240 --> 00:28:08,400
Why did you have to do this?

590
00:28:08,400 --> 00:28:09,920
Do you have any shame?

591
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:11,330
What's going on?

592
00:28:11,680 --> 00:28:13,480
A bunch of men bullying a woman.

593
00:28:13,720 --> 00:28:15,320
Yeah, what's the situation?

594
00:28:15,480 --> 00:28:16,360
Who are you?

595
00:28:16,360 --> 00:28:17,690
What are you doing here?

596
00:28:18,960 --> 00:28:19,720
This is too much.

597
00:28:19,720 --> 00:28:20,760
Is there any law?

598
00:28:20,960 --> 00:28:22,400
Yeah, stop pretending.

599
00:28:22,440 --> 00:28:24,360
I came to be a guide.

600
00:28:24,960 --> 00:28:27,160
I came to be a guide.

601
00:28:27,600 --> 00:28:30,000
What right do you have to say that about me?

602
00:28:30,080 --> 00:28:31,200
So shameless.

603
00:28:31,200 --> 00:28:32,680
Alright, stop talking.

604
00:28:32,800 --> 00:28:33,760
My man

605
00:28:35,280 --> 00:28:38,600
died on the Songhu battlefield.

606
00:28:39,760 --> 00:28:41,440
In Dachang.

607
00:28:42,640 --> 00:28:45,360
Just 26 miles away from you.

608
00:28:46,080 --> 00:28:47,920
To protect you.

609
00:28:49,440 --> 00:28:50,440
Up until now,

610
00:28:50,760 --> 00:28:52,800
his remains haven't been found.

611
00:28:55,280 --> 00:28:57,240
Bastard.

612
00:28:58,800 --> 00:29:01,480
His remains haven't even been found.

613
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:03,600
Are you crazy?

614
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:05,520
Are you still going to hit people?

615
00:29:06,200 --> 00:29:08,060
Scold them for me. Keep scolding.

616
00:29:08,920 --> 00:29:09,520
Calm down.

617
00:29:10,080 --> 00:29:11,880
You only know how to bully women.

618
00:29:12,040 --> 00:29:13,400
What kind of man are you?

619
00:29:13,800 --> 00:29:15,080
My child

620
00:29:16,200 --> 00:29:17,800
doesn't even have food to eat.

621
00:29:17,800 --> 00:29:19,560
I just wanted to be a guide

622
00:29:19,680 --> 00:29:21,120
to earn some food for him.

623
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:23,200
What did you do?

624
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:25,400
I went to sell my blood.

625
00:29:25,760 --> 00:29:28,400
I just wanted to earn some food for my child.

626
00:29:28,760 --> 00:29:30,640
But when I saw the blood donation

627
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:34,260
for the soldiers fighting the Japanese on the frontlines,

628
00:29:34,520 --> 00:29:36,200
I donated it.

629
00:29:36,840 --> 00:29:38,360
I donated it.

630
00:29:42,560 --> 00:29:45,080
The soldiers fighting at the front line,

631
00:29:45,520 --> 00:29:47,480
the blood they shed

632
00:29:48,040 --> 00:29:49,760
has a part of me in it.

633
00:29:50,240 --> 00:29:52,600
You expect us to believe you just by raising your arm?

634
00:29:52,600 --> 00:29:53,840
Do you believe him?

635
00:29:53,960 --> 00:29:54,800
Who saw it?

636
00:29:54,800 --> 00:29:55,920
Who would believe it?

637
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:57,400
I donated.

638
00:29:59,760 --> 00:30:00,760
I donated.

639
00:30:00,760 --> 00:30:02,040
Don't you have women in your family?

640
00:30:02,040 --> 00:30:03,560
What right do you have?

641
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:05,460
This is too much bullying.

642
00:30:09,240 --> 00:30:11,040
Bastard.

643
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:12,960
Get lost.

644
00:30:13,520 --> 00:30:14,560
Don't touch me.

645
00:30:16,320 --> 00:30:18,480
Shut up.

646
00:30:18,800 --> 00:30:19,360
Shut up.

647
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:20,520
Shut up.

648
00:30:21,440 --> 00:30:22,280
Forget it.

649
00:30:22,280 --> 00:30:23,160
Let's go in first.

650
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:23,760
Go in.

651
00:30:26,760 --> 00:30:27,600
Get lost.

652
00:30:27,920 --> 00:30:29,440
Don't touch me.

653
00:30:29,720 --> 00:30:31,320
You're worse than an animal.

654
00:30:31,360 --> 00:30:32,760
Who do you think you are?

655
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:33,760
Get lost.

656
00:32:15,240 --> 00:32:16,280
I know.

657
00:32:16,400 --> 00:32:18,200
You suffered a great grievance.

658
00:32:18,360 --> 00:32:19,360
It's upsetting.

659
00:32:19,960 --> 00:32:21,020
This kind of thing,

660
00:32:21,120 --> 00:32:22,480
would upset anyone.

661
00:32:22,800 --> 00:32:25,120
Pointed at and cursed by thousands.

662
00:32:25,520 --> 00:32:26,200
Yes.

663
00:32:27,120 --> 00:32:28,280
You cursed back,

664
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:30,880
but did you even touch a hair on their heads?

665
00:32:30,880 --> 00:32:33,080
You even swung that broken book around.

666
00:32:33,320 --> 00:32:34,640
Who did you hit?

667
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:36,320
You hit me with all of it.

668
00:32:38,680 --> 00:32:40,080
Speaking of being upset,

669
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:42,440
I am from Shandong.

670
00:32:43,120 --> 00:32:44,960
There is an old saying in our hometown.

671
00:32:44,960 --> 00:32:47,480
It says, kneel to heaven above and earth below,

672
00:32:47,480 --> 00:32:48,810
and parents in between.

673
00:32:49,240 --> 00:32:50,320
Other than that,

674
00:32:50,760 --> 00:32:52,040
you shouldn't kneel to anyone.

675
00:32:52,040 --> 00:32:53,680
But from my hometown in Shandong,

676
00:32:53,680 --> 00:32:55,560
I begged all the way to Shanghai.

677
00:32:55,760 --> 00:32:57,000
To survive until today,

678
00:32:57,000 --> 00:32:58,600
how many people have I kneeled to?

679
00:32:58,600 --> 00:33:00,360
If I got upset even once

680
00:33:00,360 --> 00:33:01,280
and gave up living,

681
00:33:01,280 --> 00:33:03,740
I would have died tens of thousands of times.

682
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:12,160
So,

683
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:13,240
I believe

684
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:15,360
man proposes, heaven disposes.

685
00:33:15,760 --> 00:33:18,090
There are gods three feet above our heads.

686
00:33:19,600 --> 00:33:20,520
Just think about it.

687
00:33:20,520 --> 00:33:21,850
The day we took the boat,

688
00:33:22,480 --> 00:33:23,840
if the Japanese hadn't

689
00:33:24,160 --> 00:33:26,160
dropped a bomb on the Yangtze River,

690
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:27,480
wouldn't we have been

691
00:33:27,600 --> 00:33:29,160
in Wuhan and Shanghai respectively?

692
00:33:29,160 --> 00:33:31,640
We wouldn't have anything to do with each other, right?

693
00:33:31,640 --> 00:33:33,440
But the boat was bombed.

694
00:33:33,680 --> 00:33:34,680
Well, this bombing,

695
00:33:34,680 --> 00:33:36,040
blew us all to Shanghai.

696
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:45,760
Do you still remember,

697
00:33:46,920 --> 00:33:48,850
the day we entered the concession,

698
00:33:49,440 --> 00:33:52,120
kowtowing from door to door,

699
00:33:52,560 --> 00:33:53,690
kneeling to people?

700
00:33:53,920 --> 00:33:54,720
Wasn't there still someone

701
00:33:54,720 --> 00:33:56,440
who opened a window for us?

702
00:33:57,160 --> 00:33:58,290
What does this show?

703
00:33:58,520 --> 00:34:00,050
It shows that in this world,

704
00:34:00,080 --> 00:34:02,760
some people still have a heart.

705
00:34:03,200 --> 00:34:04,520
If you get upset once

706
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:06,280
and don't want to live anymore,

707
00:34:06,280 --> 00:34:06,960
you'd be letting down

708
00:34:06,960 --> 00:34:09,290
that old lady who opened the window for us.

709
00:34:57,520 --> 00:34:59,000
We did suffer a loss.

710
00:34:59,720 --> 00:35:01,400
It is a bad thing,

711
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:03,960
but

712
00:35:05,600 --> 00:35:06,520
I don't think it's necessarily

713
00:35:06,520 --> 00:35:07,920
a bad thing.

714
00:35:10,520 --> 00:35:11,980
I've known you for so long.

715
00:35:12,680 --> 00:35:15,080
I've never seen you so energetic as today.

716
00:35:15,360 --> 00:35:16,520
Hitting whoever you catch,

717
00:35:16,520 --> 00:35:17,920
cursing whoever you see.

718
00:35:18,040 --> 00:35:18,760
In a crowd,

719
00:35:18,760 --> 00:35:20,240
I think you're a real man.

720
00:35:20,480 --> 00:35:21,720
You have that special energy in you,

721
00:35:21,720 --> 00:35:22,640
you know?

722
00:35:22,960 --> 00:35:25,120
We can't suffer a loss for nothing.

723
00:35:25,480 --> 00:35:26,740
We must learn a lesson.

724
00:35:27,080 --> 00:35:29,280
As mothers, we must set an example for Yueming.

725
00:35:29,280 --> 00:35:30,140
We must tell him

726
00:35:30,320 --> 00:35:32,360
that people must have energy when they live.

727
00:35:32,360 --> 00:35:34,320
You don't have to kneel to live.

728
00:35:35,280 --> 00:35:36,520
Right?

729
00:35:42,040 --> 00:35:43,500
Are you going to eat or not?

730
00:35:43,880 --> 00:35:46,080
If it gets cold, it will ruin my cooking.

731
00:36:19,120 --> 00:36:20,120
Not enough.

732
00:36:21,960 --> 00:36:22,800
Okay.

733
00:37:05,920 --> 00:37:06,960
Mr. Fujita,

734
00:37:07,360 --> 00:37:09,490
your visit today is really too sudden.

735
00:37:09,680 --> 00:37:12,040
You just looked at this house up and down.

736
00:37:12,280 --> 00:37:13,400
Are you satisfied?

737
00:37:14,760 --> 00:37:16,280
I am very satisfied.

738
00:37:16,800 --> 00:37:18,060
Bring that thing over.

739
00:37:19,760 --> 00:37:22,040
This is the best example

740
00:37:22,280 --> 00:37:24,120
of our Sino-Japanese goodwill.

741
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:25,520
I give it to you.

742
00:37:40,800 --> 00:37:42,800
Coexistence and co-prosperity.

743
00:37:42,800 --> 00:37:43,480
Good.

744
00:37:44,240 --> 00:37:45,720
Thank you.

745
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:51,360
Come.

746
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:52,040
Come.

747
00:37:52,480 --> 00:37:53,240
Come.

748
00:37:59,400 --> 00:38:00,280
Mr. Fujita,

749
00:38:00,520 --> 00:38:02,080
because your visit is too sudden,

750
00:38:02,080 --> 00:38:03,880
these dishes are prepared a bit hastily.

751
00:38:03,880 --> 00:38:06,200
I'll ask my wife to cook a few more dishes for you.

752
00:38:06,200 --> 00:38:07,000
Wait a moment.

753
00:38:07,960 --> 00:38:09,120
Eat more.

754
00:38:09,440 --> 00:38:10,570
Thank you very much.

755
00:38:12,520 --> 00:38:13,080
How is it?

756
00:38:13,160 --> 00:38:14,420
Are these dishes today

757
00:38:14,560 --> 00:38:15,560
enough?

758
00:38:16,480 --> 00:38:17,320
What should we do?

759
00:38:17,320 --> 00:38:18,600
The Japanese came so suddenly.

760
00:38:18,600 --> 00:38:20,160
If Dad comes back at this time,

761
00:38:20,160 --> 00:38:21,240
and they suddenly bump into each other,

762
00:38:21,240 --> 00:38:22,160
we are dead meat.

763
00:38:22,160 --> 00:38:23,400
Are you stupid?

764
00:38:23,560 --> 00:38:25,480
Today is sister-in-law's first day at work.

765
00:38:25,480 --> 00:38:26,600
Don't mention it.

766
00:38:26,720 --> 00:38:27,880
I want to beat myself.

767
00:38:27,880 --> 00:38:28,920
Dad was worried

768
00:38:28,920 --> 00:38:30,560
so he went to the alley to pick her up from work.

769
00:38:30,560 --> 00:38:32,090
He won't be back for a while.

770
00:38:32,280 --> 00:38:33,200
How do you know?

771
00:38:33,200 --> 00:38:35,060
What if they bump into each other?

772
00:38:35,440 --> 00:38:37,000
It's good if they do.

773
00:38:37,160 --> 00:38:37,920
Think about it.

774
00:38:37,920 --> 00:38:39,380
When Dad loses his temper,

775
00:38:39,520 --> 00:38:41,360
he will definitely start cursing.

776
00:38:41,360 --> 00:38:41,920
That Fujita

777
00:38:41,920 --> 00:38:43,720
might say he is an anti-Japanese element.

778
00:38:43,720 --> 00:38:45,360
Then we won't need to anonymously report

779
00:38:45,360 --> 00:38:47,490
the leaflets you stuffed in his place.

780
00:38:47,600 --> 00:38:48,930
Are you out of your mind?

781
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:50,690
If we report Dad ourselves,

782
00:38:50,800 --> 00:38:53,040
he will at most be arrested by the police station,

783
00:38:53,040 --> 00:38:54,320
reprimanded, and locked up for two days.

784
00:38:54,320 --> 00:38:56,080
We can take the opportunity to get the title deed.

785
00:38:56,080 --> 00:38:57,840
If Dad meets the Japanese,

786
00:38:58,040 --> 00:38:58,920
with his temper,

787
00:38:58,920 --> 00:38:59,880
hitting and cursing,

788
00:38:59,880 --> 00:39:00,920
what if he kills a Japanese?

789
00:39:00,920 --> 00:39:02,000
We'll be doomed.

790
00:39:02,600 --> 00:39:04,880
Not likely. He's just an old man.

791
00:39:05,440 --> 00:39:06,720
Go, quick.

792
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:07,520
Wait.

793
00:39:07,920 --> 00:39:08,720
Remember,

794
00:39:08,880 --> 00:39:10,440
if Uncle comes back,

795
00:39:10,440 --> 00:39:11,560
you must send him away.

796
00:39:11,560 --> 00:39:12,640
Don't let him come up under any circumstances.

797
00:39:12,640 --> 00:39:14,240
Got it.

798
00:39:14,240 --> 00:39:15,720
Bravo,

799
00:39:17,720 --> 00:39:19,920
Miss Yoko. What a dance.

800
00:39:20,720 --> 00:39:21,800
Impressive.

801
00:39:21,840 --> 00:39:22,560
Mr. Zhang,

802
00:39:22,960 --> 00:39:24,080
when can we

803
00:39:24,160 --> 00:39:25,840
complete the transfer process

804
00:39:25,840 --> 00:39:29,520
for this house?

805
00:39:30,680 --> 00:39:32,720
I will do it as soon as possible.

806
00:39:33,320 --> 00:39:35,320
But Mr. Fujita,

807
00:39:35,400 --> 00:39:36,280
to be honest,

808
00:39:36,560 --> 00:39:40,920
there are some small family matters regarding this house

809
00:39:41,000 --> 00:39:42,400
that I need to handle.

810
00:39:42,640 --> 00:39:43,960
I have to ask you

811
00:39:44,320 --> 00:39:46,000
to give me a little more time.

812
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:54,080
Wait a moment.

813
00:39:59,560 --> 00:40:01,200
Well, Yoko,

814
00:40:01,600 --> 00:40:03,560
do you really like this house?

815
00:40:04,360 --> 00:40:05,200
Yes.

816
00:40:06,800 --> 00:40:08,600
Then let's live here.

817
00:40:09,120 --> 00:40:10,040
Really?

818
00:40:10,680 --> 00:40:12,840
Have you thought about how to decorate this house?

819
00:40:12,840 --> 00:40:14,280
Yes.

820
00:40:15,600 --> 00:40:17,920
This place has good lighting.

821
00:40:18,160 --> 00:40:20,480
I want to put flowers here.

822
00:40:21,240 --> 00:40:23,680
I'll make a tatami mat for tea ceremony here.

823
00:40:23,680 --> 00:40:29,480
That room can be my dance practice room.

824
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:33,360
Mr. Fujita,

825
00:40:34,680 --> 00:40:35,880
look at this.

826
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:38,960
This is a rare book from the Song Dynasty

827
00:40:38,960 --> 00:40:40,640
of China,

828
00:40:40,760 --> 00:40:42,080
'Records of Mount Lu'.

829
00:40:42,760 --> 00:40:44,440
See if you like it.

830
00:40:54,720 --> 00:40:55,640
Mr. Zhang,

831
00:40:56,560 --> 00:40:57,840
you're amazing.

832
00:40:58,240 --> 00:41:01,240
This is a very rare ancient Chinese book, right?

833
00:41:02,000 --> 00:41:03,360
I like it very much.

834
00:41:07,200 --> 00:41:10,160
But does this have any

835
00:41:10,320 --> 00:41:12,640
inevitable connection with the house?

836
00:41:12,760 --> 00:41:14,440
Is there a problem with the transaction?

837
00:41:14,440 --> 00:41:16,040
There won't be any problems.

838
00:41:16,040 --> 00:41:16,720
Please rest assured,

839
00:41:16,720 --> 00:41:19,400
I will definitely complete the transaction legally and reasonably.

840
00:41:19,400 --> 00:41:20,600
It's just that this 'Records of Mount Lu',

841
00:41:20,600 --> 00:41:21,440
I...

842
00:41:26,800 --> 00:41:29,840
I will wait until the handover is complete,

843
00:41:29,960 --> 00:41:31,820
then I will give it to you as a gift.

844
00:41:37,640 --> 00:41:39,640
By then, we will jointly build

845
00:41:40,040 --> 00:41:42,920
a friendship of co-prosperity and coexistence.

846
00:41:45,720 --> 00:41:46,760
That's good.

847
00:41:47,320 --> 00:41:50,000
Then thank you for your great hospitality.

848
00:41:50,320 --> 00:41:52,480
I'll wait for your good news.

849
00:41:53,200 --> 00:41:54,720
Wait for my good news.

850
00:41:58,600 --> 00:42:02,960
This looks just like my house in Tokyo.

851
00:42:04,200 --> 00:42:05,080
Yeah.

852
00:42:05,440 --> 00:42:08,440
It seems we are destined to have this house.

853
00:42:09,200 --> 00:42:10,840
Of course.

854
00:42:11,880 --> 00:42:14,200
Our destiny of Sino-Japanese goodwill,

855
00:42:14,360 --> 00:42:16,560
I think it should start with this house.

856
00:42:16,840 --> 00:42:17,680
Mr. Fujita,

857
00:42:17,920 --> 00:42:18,680
cheers.

858
00:42:18,880 --> 00:42:19,760
Cheers.

859
00:42:32,360 --> 00:42:33,320
Shuyuan,

860
00:42:34,160 --> 00:42:35,560
has Yujiao come back yet?

861
00:42:35,840 --> 00:42:36,520
Not yet.

862
00:42:36,880 --> 00:42:38,160
I just wanted to grab a bite

863
00:42:38,160 --> 00:42:39,280
and go out to pick you up.

864
00:42:39,280 --> 00:42:41,560
How come you came back by yourself, Uncle?

865
00:42:41,560 --> 00:42:44,640
Isn't it Yujiao's first time going out to work?

866
00:42:44,680 --> 00:42:46,040
I'm a little worried.

867
00:42:46,320 --> 00:42:48,120
It rained so hard just now.

868
00:42:48,240 --> 00:42:49,520
I wanted to go meet her.

869
00:42:49,760 --> 00:42:51,360
We probably missed each other.

870
00:42:51,360 --> 00:42:52,120
With this weather,

871
00:42:52,120 --> 00:42:53,650
I reckon it will rain again.

872
00:42:53,760 --> 00:42:56,000
We can't let Sister-in-law get caught in the rain again.

873
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:57,480
Let's go out and meet her.

874
00:42:57,520 --> 00:42:58,080
